INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2371, 'The Annals of Darrowshire\n\nDarrowshire, named from the Darrowmere Lake to its west, is a village tucked into the southern foothills of Lordaeron.  Known for humble yet hardworking residents, Darrowshire stayed in the background of Lordaeron history until the Second War.\n\nHeroes were made during that war.  And heroes were lost.\n', 2372, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2372, 'The Battle of Darrowshire\n\nThe Battle of Darrowshire took place in the middle of the Second War, when scourge forces rampaged across Lordaeron.  Darrowshire was cut off from the bulk of Alliance forces, but the town was bolstered by a company of troops, a contingent of paladins of the Silver Hand, and a staunch group of local militia led by Captain Joseph Redpath.', 2373, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2373, 'The Scourge\'s first assaults on Darrowshire were sparse.  Small groups of marauding skeletons and corpses wandered the outskirts of the village and were repelled.  \n\nBut the Scourge were not balked by the defenders\' tenacity, and responded in kind; soon after the first wave of attacks a second wave emerged.  Champion ghouls, servants of the ghoul lord Horgus, screamed down from the hills and clashed with beleaguered Darrowshire defenders.', 2374, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2374, 'The Defenders weakened, but were relieved by paladins, disciples of the Silver Hand.  Their leader, Davil Crokford, was a native of Darrowshire.  He brought his followers to the village when he heard of the impending attack, and together with the defenders they held back the servants of Horgus.\n\nWhen Horgus himself entered the battle, he met with Davil.  For many minutes they fought and Davil eventually prevailed, but he suffered a mortal wound and died soon after defeating the ghoul lord.', 2375, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2375, 'The battle continued, and Captain Redpath led his militia bravely.  And it might have been won, had the captain not been corrupted by the death knight Marduk the Black.\n\nIn the middle of the fray Marduk rode up to Redpath, and with black magic he tore loose Redpath\'s spirit, twisting it into an evil shadow of the brave captain.', 2376, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2376, 'The corrupted Captain Redpath then spread his evil taint among the defenders of Darrowshire, who betrayed their allies and slaughtered them.  They then turned on the town of Darrowshire and killed all who hid in their homes.\n\nThe remaining scourge army, along with the corrupted spirit of Captain Redpath, then left the ravaged village of Darrowshire and tore into Lordaeron, adding to the pain and death of the Second War.', 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2377, 'The Annals of Darrowshire\n\nDarrowshire, named from the Darrowmere Lake to its west, is a village tucked into the southern foothills of Lordaeron.  Known for humble yet hardworking residents, Darrowshire stayed in the background of Lordaeron history until the Second War.\n\nHeroes were made during that war.  And heroes were lost.', 2378, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2378, 'The Battle of Darrowshire\n\nThe Battle of Darrowshire took place in the middle of the Second War, when scourge forces rampaged across Lordaeron.  Darrowshire was cut off from the bulk of Alliance forces, but the town was bolstered by a company of troops, a contingent of paladins of the Silver Hand, and a staunch group of local militia led by Captain Joseph Redpath.', 2379, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2379, 'The Scourge\'s first assaults on Darrowshire were sparse.  Small groups of marauding skeletons and corpses wandered the outskirts of the village and were easily defeated.  \n\nBut the Scourge sensed the defenders\' tenacity, and responded in kind; soon after the first wave of attacks a second wave emerged.  Champion ghouls, servants of the ghoul lord Horgus, screamed down from the hills and clashed with beleaguered Darrowshire defenders.', 2380, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2380, 'The Defenders weakened, but were relieved by paladins, disciples of the Silver Hand.  Their leader, Davil Crokford, was a native of Darrowshire.  He brought his followers to the village when he heard of the impending attack, and together with the defenders they held back the servants of Horgus.\n\nWhen Horgus himself entered the battle, he met with Davil.  For many minutes they fought and Davil eventually prevailed, but he suffered a mortal wound and died soon after defeating the ghoul lord.', 2381, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2381, 'The battle continued, and Captain Redpath led his militia bravely.  And it might have been won, had the captain not been corrupted by the death knight Marduk the Black.\n\nIn the middle of the fray Marduk rode up to Redpath, and with black magic he tore loose Redpath\'s spirit, twisting it into an evil shadow of the brave captain.', 2382, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2382, 'The corrupted Captain Redpath then spread his evil taint among the defenders of Darrowshire, who betrayed their allies and slaughtered them.  They then turned on the town of Darrowshire and killed all who hid in their homes.\n\nThe remaining scourge army, along with the corrupted spirit of Captain Redpath, then left the ravaged village of Darrowshire and tore into Lordaeron, adding to the pain and death of the Second War.', 2383, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2383, 'The Fate of Horgus the Ravager\n\nHorgus the Ravager fell at the Battle of Darrowshire.  But the evil within him was not fully spent.  The victorious Scourge forces removed his skull from the battlefield of Darrowshire, carrying it with them to sow dread among the living they faced.\n\nDays later, the company of Scourge who possessed the head were defeated by Silver Hand Paladins.  Horgus\' head was cast into Blackwood Lake.', 2384, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2384, 'The Fate of Marduk the Black\n\nMarduk survived the Second War, causing great death and suffering with his foul, rune-laden sword.  Although Marduk still lives, his sword was lost in a battle near Corin\'s Crossing.  A dwarf captain shattered the sword on his enchanted shield, forcing Marduk to flee the field and winning the day for the Alliance.\n\nMarduk\'s sword sank into the earth and corrupted it, eating a gorge into the land, now known as the Infectis Scar.', 2385, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2385, 'The Fate of Davil Lightfire\n\nDavil Lightfire died at the Battle of Darrowshire, but his bravery inspired the Alliance throughout the war.\n\nHis book, his paladin\'s libram, was recovered by Scarlet Crusade troops.  It now resides in the town hall of the Scarlet Crusade controlled Hearthglen, often read by crusaders eager to draw from Davil\'s strength.', 2386, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2386, 'The Fate of Joseph Redpath\n\nJoseph Redpath was killed during the Battle of Darrowshire.  His spirit was corrupted and took new shape, and this creature spread great evil in Lordaeron.\n\nAt Gahrron\'s Withering, east of Andorhal, the corrupted Redpath was finally defeated by Alliance forces.  His shield still rests near the barn of the plagued farmstead, and Scourge minions are still drawn to the memory of his evil.', 2391, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2390, 'The Fate of Joseph Redpath Joseph Redpath was killed during the Battle of Darrowshire.  His spirit was corrupted and took new shape, and this creature spread great evil in Lordaeron. At Gahrron\'s Withering, east of Andorhal, the corrupted Redpath was finally defeated by Alliance forces.  His shield still rests near the barn of the plagued farmstead, and Scourge minions are still drawn to the memory of his evil. ', 2391, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2391, 'The Fate of Carlin Redpath\n\nBrother to Captain Joseph Redpath, Carlin fell during the battle of Darrowshire.  But although terribly wounded, he was not slain.\n\nDays after the battle, agents of the Argent Dawn found Carlin wandering, weak from thirst and fever, near Corin\'s Crossing.  They tended to his wounds and brought him to the Light\'s Hope Chapel.\n\nGrateful for their charity, Carlin joined the ranks of the Argent Dawn and now fights a battle of revenge against the Scourge.', 0, 0, 0, 25928);
INSERT INTO `page_text` VALUES (2410, 'The Fate of Carlin Redpath Brother to Captain Joseph Redpath, Carlin fell during the battle of Darrowshire.  But although terribly wounded, he was not slain. Days after the battle, agents of the Argent Dawn found Carlin wandering, weak from thirst and fever, near Corin\'s Crossing.  They tended to his wounds and brought him to the Light\'s Hope Chapel. Grateful for their charity, Carlin joined the ranks of the Argent Dawn and now fights a battle of revenge against the Scourge. ', 0, 0, 0, 0);
